	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=29370><span id=Scholar>paugod</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>28 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.26]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Has anybody noticed that in this Allakhazam section the number one posting area under class, as of this writing, is Druid at 2612, number two is Paladin at 2174 and number three is Monk at 1853 with the lowest the Wiz at 605 posts? Does this indicate popularity of our class? Probably not.<br><br>All outside inquiries into the number of characters making up Everquest have repeatedly shown that Druids are the most popular but the next popular class has usually been Warriors and Rangers. And yet, the number of posts here indicate that the next greatest exchange of class data is for Paladins. The reason is somewhat obvious that playing a "pure" role type like a warrior is just that - plain and straight forward. Some might say easy. Whereas playing a hybrid like Druids, Paladins and even a Monk takes a bit of doing and old fashion work, and yes, even sophistication. Sophistication? You bet because anyone can be a Warrior, a Wiz, a Bard but being a Paladin is a struggle and the reward of this effort is truly an interesting bit of game playing. Eh?<br><br> <br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>Alarick<br>Paladin Lvl 45<br>Forbringers of Fate</td></td></tr>
